Scout's family did everything right. They got him to the emergency vet quickly, consented to the diagnostics, and then hit the same wall so many families hit: the cost of continuing.

## The turning point

With the case now fully funded, Scout's team can focus on treatment decisions instead of payment timing.

## What funded means here

Scout's case demonstrates the middle state that many families need to see: not every emergency is a one-day story. Funded means the immediate care is covered and the family has room to focus on recovery.
